# Guidelines for shellscripting implementation

0. Use TDD - create unit tests using bats framework
1. All scripts should be written in bash.
2. All scripts should be written in a way that is easy to understand and maintain.
3. All scripts should be written in a way that is easy to test.
4. All scripts should be written in a way that is easy to deploy.
5. All scripts should be written in a way that is easy to debug.
6. IF a script that modifies files or directories on failure, it should be written in
7. a way that is easy to rollback.
8. Max of 2 level nesting
9. 2 spaces tabbing
10. Every script created must pass shellcheck check.
11. All scripts must be unit tested. Test commands should be sent to execute_command mcp
